Forms in Bootstrap
-----------------------------
Html Forms are a part of web pages and web applications.
creating form layout or styling form controls manually one by one using css will be time consuming and tedious proces.
Bootstrap simplifies the process of styling and alignment of form controls like labels, input fileds,... using predefined set of classes.


Bootstrap provides form layouts

Vertical Form (default)
Horizontal Form
Inline Form


Creating Vertical Form Layout
---------------------------------------------
To create vertical form layout use predefined margin utility class for grouping labels, form controls,...

all input controls requires form-control class

select tag requires form-select class

SR
Srinivasa Rao
09:25 AM
<html>
<head>
<title>Forms</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
<form>
<div class="row mb-3">
<div class="col-sm-4">
<label>Enter User name:</label>
</div>
<div class="col-sm-8">
<input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter user name">
</div>
</div>
<div class="row mb-3">
<div class="col-sm-4">
<label>Enter Password :</label>
</div>
<div class="col-sm-8">
<input type="password" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter password">
</div>
</div>
<input type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" value="Login">
</form>
</div>
</body>
</html>

